# Plan-Phase Scaffold Gate

## Rule

Before any `/DEVELOP` command runs, the following must exist:

1. `docs/workspace/plans/scaffold/PROJECT_SCAFFOLD.md` — full annotated file tree
2. `scripts/scaffold.sh` — runnable script that creates the tree
3. The scaffold script must have been confirmed (user typed `yes` to apply it)

## Why This Rule Exists

Building without a scaffold causes:
- Files created in wrong locations across different tools and agents
- Inconsistent naming that breaks imports
- Missing config files discovered mid-build
- Architectural drift between planning docs and actual structure
- Parallel agent work streams stepping on each other

## Scaffold Completeness Requirements

`PROJECT_SCAFFOLD.md` must contain:
- Every directory the project will use (including empty ones)
- Every file that will exist at completion (stubs acceptable, paths are not negotiable)
- Owner agent annotation per directory
- Phase annotation (which SDD phase creates each file)
- Config file inventory: env files, tsconfig, package.json, CI workflows, etc.
- Database migration file locations
- Test file locations mirroring src/ structure
- Public/static asset directory structure

## Enforcement

`/DEVELOP start` checks for scaffold existence.
If `PROJECT_SCAFFOLD.md` is missing → halt + output:

```
❌ Scaffold not found.
The full project file structure must be defined before development begins.
This ensures every AI tool and agent knows exactly where files go.

→ Run /PLAN scaffold to generate it now.
```

## Scaffold Script Format

`scripts/scaffold.sh` must be a valid bash script using `mkdir -p` and `touch`.
It must be idempotent (safe to run multiple times).
It must NOT delete existing files.

## Exception

If the project already has existing `src/` code (brownfield project),
run `/SCAN scaffold` instead to reverse-engineer the current structure
into `PROJECT_SCAFFOLD.md` and confirm alignment with planning docs.
